<P>David Serving His GENERATION.</P>
<P>Or, A SERMON Shewing What is to be done in order to our &s;o Serving our <HI>Generation,</HI> as that when we Dy, we &s;hall Enter into a Ble&s;&s;ed <HI>REST.</HI></P>
<P>(Wherein Some account is given concerning many Eminent Mini&s;ters of Chri&s;t at <HI>London,</HI> as well as in <HI>N.E.</HI> lately gone to their <HI>Re&s;t.</HI>) Occa&s;ioned by the Death, of the Reverend Mr. JOHN BAILY, Who Decea&s;ed at <HI>Bo&s;ton</HI> in <HI>New-England. December</HI> 12<HI>th.</HI> 1697.</P>
<P>By <HI>Increa&s;e Mather, <HI>Pre&s;ident of</HI></HI> Harvard Colledge.</P>
<Q><BIBL><HI>Numb. 20.29.</HI></BIBL>
<P>When all the Congregation &s;aw that Aaron was dead, they mourned for Aaron thirty dayes, even all the hou&s;e of I&s;rael.</P></Q>
<P><HI>Bo&s;ton,</HI> Printed by <HI>B. Green,</HI> &amp; <HI>J. Allen.</HI> 1698</P>
